<br>
My character's original surname was Dejecta. Around the time he reached level 20 the person that played his in game wife decided to no longer play that character, and in roleplaying her dying, it seemed appropriate (dejecta=brokenhearted.) After a while I decided to get rid of the surname though; I didn't want that one incident to dominate his life. So from about level 25 or so to level 50 I had no surname.<br>
<br>
At level 50 I decided to take on another surname. Gramosk' now long dead wife's name was Silvaris, so I decided to incorporate that into his surname. He is a member of the Koada'Vie, so I incorporated that. Lastly, I decided to use the name Elar (actually an anagram of the main character's name from a concept album from my favorite musical group.)<br>
<br>
So I put them together, originally as Elar'Vie'Sil, but later, when the gm told me I could only have one apostrophe, I modified that to Elarvie'Siil.<br>
<br>
