~~<i>Hand of the Gods~~ </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/usandain.showPublicProfile>Sandain</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/17/00 12:05:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgodsmightroleplaytavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=48>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.primemedia.net/pages/~jwood/cot/sandain/sandain_small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How did I come up with my name? :)</span><hr size=1> Back when 14.4 modems were &quot;the shit&quot;, I was known by the alias Knightraider on the BBSs I visited.  This name had more downfalls then I cared for (similar to a name of a TV show around the same time).  I grew older, and the new BBSs were now known as IRC.  I picked Sole, no real or good reason behind it, but it did have kind of a nice ring to it.  The problem I had with this name was a lot of spanish speaking people would talk to me (I don't speak Spanish <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).  When EQ came out, I decided it was time for a new name, and this time I let the name generator pick my name.  I wanted one that was easy to remember and easy to spell.  Sandain came up, it sounded like an elven paladin, so it stuck.  When I reached 20, I spent a while trying to figure out what I wanted my last name to be.  I wanted a name that not only went well with Sandain, but sounded like a name that a paladin would have.  Whiteblade came out of my think tank <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  Paladins and white seem to go together, so the name stuck.  <br>
<br>
