</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uberton.showPublicProfile>Berton</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/8/00 9:33:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgodsmightroleplaytavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=49>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How did I come up with my name? :)</span><hr size=1> Last October I was called home for emergency leave when my Grandfather passed on. He was very dear to me and I was deeply saddened. Upon my return home I decided to try this game called Everquest out to take my mind off my sorrow. During character selection my natural choice was a Paladin. When I got to the name I thought it would be fitting of such a kind and thoughtful man that I name this Paladin I was creating after him. Berton was my Grandfathers actual name and my character is a tribute to him. My surname is a variation of my family name with a Native American twist (My grandfathers hobby was Native American lore). Thus the surname Strongheart. <p>Berton Strongheart 51st Cavalier<BR>Stroh Tanglefoot 30th Druid<BR>Sanctuary<BR>Nameless<BR>"You will not evade me, Ayanosuke!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uklemara.showPublicProfile>Klemara</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/9/00 12:27:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgodsmightroleplaytavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.home.earthlink.net/~jerrigaither/eqpics/klempic2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How did I come up with my name? :)</span><hr size=1> My first name, Klemara, was quite simply guessed. It took me several days to come up with it, but it was entirely madeup.<br>
<br>
My maiden name, Palisade, I researched quite a bit. I didn't want the typical &quot;Holygrail&quot; or &quot;Braveheart&quot; and such.<br>
Palisade, in short, is an area of protection... a fortress of sort.<br>
<br>
My married name, Dae'Mela, is the history of my calling. I am married to a dark elf necromancer. Since I wed a dark man, and he a light woman, we have decided to walk in the shadows of good and evil. Dae'Mela is elvish for shadow love.<br>
<br>
