Then came my Paladin. He was my second choice. (was always anyway if mage sucked) Since my mage was a high elf and I love the role play of a stuck up elf with honor/respect to others I choose a weak stick looking elf. Boy did I have a blast with this fellow. I choose the name Lynthalis for his name. I could tank so much better and heal with LoH. I was very respected as a newbie <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  As I got older and grouped with people I knew; I aqquired new friends. During that time, my friends called me Lyn for short which made me sound girlish <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  They decided to add something to my name, the &quot;in&quot; into it. So now I changed my name to Lynin, but I will always keep Lynthalis. Not much of a story or anything. Just something I wanted to post since everyone else did and I liked it.<br>
